Utterances.UttText: HPI:  Gerry Cage is a 46-year old male with a history of HTN who presents today with a complaint of chest pain.

Phrases.PhraseText: a 46-year old male with a history of HTN
today with a complaint of chest pain.

Utterances.UttText: Patient notes that approximately 3 days ago he noted some chest pain while moving groceries.
Patient describes the pain as being a deep ache and notes heaviness in the center of the chest during this episode.

Phrases.PhraseText: heaviness in the center of the chest

Utterances.UttText: Patient notes that pain was resolved after 5-10 minutes.
Patient states that he has had similar episodes over the last 4 months, but these episodes did not produce this level of pain/pressure.

Phrases.PhraseText: similar episodes over the last 4 months,

Utterances.UttText: Also notes history of abdominal/chest pain after eating heavy meals over the last 1 year.

Phrases.PhraseText: after eating heavy meals over the last 1 year.

Utterances.UttText: Denies SOB, diarrhea, vomiting, exertional dyspnea.
ROS otherwise negative.

Medications: Chlorthalidone 25mg once per day, lisinopril 10 mg once per day Allergies: None  PMH: HTN, no recent infections, no history of surgeries, or hospitalizations FH: Father had multiple heart attacks in 40's.
Mother had history of hypertension, diabetes, and breast cancer SH:  Patient works at capital one in IT department.
Patient smokes 1 pack of cigarettes per day over the last 20 years.  patient drinks 2-3 glass of wine 1-2 days per week.
